1.en: Once you're looking at an encyclopaedia page, hyperlinks can take you to any other informating in there.
1.cn: 你在查看百科全书页面时，高级链接可以让你查找其他信息。

2.en: You can specify standard message class names only for forms that add a new page to a form or that are appended to the bottom of a form.
2.cn: 您只能针对可将新页面加入至表单的表单，或是附加至表单底部的表单，指定标准讯息类别名称。

3.en: When Jane went off to get his order he took a newspaper out of his coat pocket and began reading the sports page on the back.
3.cn: 当简离开准备他的餐点时，他从大衣里拿出了一张报纸，然后从背面的体育版开始读起。

0.en: Someone joined our page. We have an actual fan.
0.cn: 但有人加了我们的粉丝页，我们有一个粉丝了。

1.en: Now I'd like you to turn to page 1. Now I'd like you to read from page 1 to 48.
1.cn: 现在请翻回到第1页，现在请大家从第1页读到第48页。

2.en: Okay, fine. I'm checking her Facebook page.
2.cn: 好吧，我是在看她的主页。

3.en: That's not an email. That's Leslie's Facebook page.
3.cn: 才不是邮件呢，你在看莱斯利的FACEBOOK主页。

4.en: So I'd like you guys to open your books to page 48.

5.en: I just need one page. Which page can we use? News, sports, fashion. Not the fashion page. OK, I'll use the business page.
5.cn: 我只需要一张纸。哪页是我们不要的？新闻版，体育版，噢对了，时尚版。不要用我的时尚版。好吧，那我们就用商业版。

6.en: My first 10 page paper, they didn't assign those in my high school.
6.cn: 我的第一份十页论文，高中没人会布置这么长的作业。

7.en: I don't know, there were a lot of pictures, and one page only had the word "Brakkadoom!"
7.cn: 大部分都只是图片啊，有一页上甚至只写了一句"受死吧"。

8.en: Word of warning page 73. I don't understand. It makes no sense. It looks impossible.
8.cn: 提醒一下，是第73页的。我完全不明白，说不通啊，不可能啊。

9.en: Oh, this is cool. So, a few weeks ago, I set up a fan page on Facebook for our band and...
9.cn: 这挺酷，几周前呢，我在脸书上给我们乐团开了个粉丝页...

10.en: Okay, so for tonight's assignment, I'd like you to write me a three-page essay on anything.
10.cn: 听好，今晚的家庭作业是请大家写一篇三页的论文，题目不限。

11.en: Page 14, item seven. So, what's for dinner? A side of corn succotash. Hmm. Interesting.
11.cn: 第14页，第7条。那么我们到底吃什么？一份豆煮玉米。真有意思。

12.en: What I wanted to talk about was how on page 1 of your book, you say you had hard time not bringing your work home.
12.cn: 我想说的是，在你书的第一页，你为什么会说很难不把工作带回家做呢。

13.en: Without you here to shame me, I watched every Real Housewives episode and I only got to page two in War And Peace.
13.cn: 没有你在旁边取笑我，我已堕落到看完全部《贵妇的真实生活》，正经书却才看了两页。

14.en: This is not happening. Be that as it may, page nine says that you have to provide me with lemon-flavored sparkling waters, so chop-chop.
14.cn: 这不是真的。即便是这样，第九页写着你得为我提供柠檬味的气泡水，所以赶紧的…

15.en: Okay, hold on. Page 18 of the surrogacy contract, Tara, you specifically agreed to terminate if there were substantial signs of birth defects.
15.cn: 好了，冷静点，代孕合同第18页，塔拉你特别同意了若有足够证据证明孩子先天缺陷则终止妊娠。

16.en: From 'Rule Britannia' to 'Cool Britannia', the fabric and the skyline of this city is forever turning over a new page, which is, after all, what every great story should do.
16.cn: 从「大不列颠的统治」到「大不列颠的风格」，这个城市的高楼大厦和建筑正不断地揭开新的一页，这正是所有伟大城市的必经过程。

17.en: Is that guy on your Facebook page, is he gonna be there? Who?
17.cn: 你脸书主页上的那个人也会去吗？谁？

18.en: That light means it's on? It doesn't automatically turn off when you go to a different web page?
18.cn: 亮灯表示开着吗？我关掉网页时摄像头不会自动关掉吗？

19.en: Penny? Well, it's a little juvenile. I mean, it kind of looks like the MySpace page of a 13-year-old girl.
19.cn: 佩妮？呃，有一点点幼稚，看着像一个13岁女孩的个人主页。
